You said:
When setting up in the developers app facebook it says invalid privacy policy even tho i made one in docs
ChatGPT said:

The error you're getting—"Invalid Privacy Policy URL"—is happening because Facebook does not accept Google Docs or Google Drive links as valid privacy policy URLs. It requires a publicly accessible web URL, preferably on your own domain, that displays the privacy policy in standard HTML format.

Here’s how to fix it:

Option 1: Host on your own website

If you have a website or landing page for your app or business, do this:

  1. Create a new page (e.g., yourdomain.com/privacy-policy)

  2. Paste the privacy policy text there

  3. Make sure the page is publicly accessible (not behind a login)

  4. Copy that URL and paste it into the Facebook App’s “Privacy Policy URL” field

Option 2: Use a free HTML hosting platform

If you don’t have a website yet, here are quick alternatives:

  • GitHub Pages (for developers): You can host a simple HTML file for free.

  • Netlify or Vercel: Upload a static HTML page containing your privacy policy.

  • Carrd.co: Create a free one-page site and paste your privacy policy there.

Would you like me to generate a simple HTML file of your privacy policy that you can upload to one of these services?

You said:
How do I do it on GitHub Pages?
ChatGPT said:

Here’s a simple step-by-step guide to host your Privacy Policy using GitHub Pages—totally free and publicly accessible:

Step 1: Create a GitHub Account (if you don’t have one)

  • Go to https://github.com and sign up for an account.

Step 2: Create a New Repository

  1. After logging in, click the "+" icon at the top right > New repository

  2. Name the repository something like: privacy-policy

  3. Set it to Public

  4. Check "Add a README file"

  5. Click Create repository

Step 3: Add Your Privacy Policy as an HTML File

  1. In the repository, click "Add file" > "Create new file"

  2. Name the file: index.html

  3. Paste the following HTML code (with your privacy policy inside):

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 10/9/2024</p>
  <p>FurniStore values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information when you use our app, <strong>[Your App Name]</strong>, accessible through Facebook.</p>
  <p>By using our app, you agree to the collection and use of your information as described in this policy.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect different types of information to improve our services and provide a better experience.</p>

  <h3>a. Personal Information</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Full name</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Phone number</li>
    <li>Facebook profile information (as permitted by your privacy settings)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>b. Usage Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your device’s IP address</li>
    <li>Browser type and version</li>
    <li>Pages visited within our app</li>
    <li>Time and date of your visit</li>
    <li>App interactions and preferences</li>
    <li>Other technical data for diagnostics and analytics</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>c. Information from Facebook</h3>
  <p>If you log in using Facebook, we may access certain information you share with us based on your Facebook privacy settings, such as your name, profile picture, and friends list (if applicable).</p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Providing, maintaining, and improving our app</li>
    <li>Customizing your user experience</li>
    <li>Sending important notifications, updates, and promotional content (if you opt-in)</li>
    <li>Responding to customer support inquiries</li>
    <li>Monitoring app performance and fixing technical issues</li>
    <li>Ensuring security and preventing fraudulent activities</li>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>

  1. Scroll down and click “Commit new file”

Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages

  1. Go to the Settings tab of your repository

  2. Scroll down to “Pages”

  3. Under Source, select “Deploy from a branch”

  4. Choose:

    • Branch: main

    • Folder: /root

  5. Click Save

Step 5: Get Your Privacy Policy URL

After a few seconds, GitHub will give you a public link like:

arduino
https://yourusername.github.io/privacy-policy/

Use that URL in your Facebook App’s “Privacy Policy URL” field.
